# Atlas artifact signing pubkey - Ed25519 (32 bytes, 64 hex chars).
#
# PLACEHOLDER - DO NOT SHIP.
#
# This file gets compiled into the desktop client at build time via
# `include_str!` in src-tauri/src/fetcher/signing.rs. Whatever value is
# here is what clients trust for `manifest.json.sig` verification.
#
# To rotate for production:
#   1. On an air-gapped machine (or in CI secrets), run
#      `cargo run --bin atlas-build -- keygen` to emit a pkcs8 private
#      key + the matching hex pubkey.
#   2. Store the private key only in HM's CI secret store.
#   3. Replace the hex below with the pubkey.
#   4. Ship a new Atlas client - old clients can't mount artifacts
#      signed by the rotated key (which is the intended behavior).
#
# DEV KEY - paired with D:/CodeProjects/Atlas-loop-test/test-key.pem.
# Replace with the real HM pubkey before shipping.
4300ed47961370c9fd204f332cf967c3a00042443e60112aedcab64e8feae49a
